      <h3 class="ch-h3">Money-saving strategies</h3>
      <ul class="ch-bullets">
        <li><strong>Use PTE instead of IELTS / OET.</strong> Save AUD $200 on your English proficiency test.</li>
        <li><strong>Credit card for all payments.</strong> Avoid transaction failures on international payments.</li>
        <li><strong>Group accommodation for the clinical exam.</strong> Save AUD $150 – $200 per week by sharing with other candidates.</li>
        <li><strong>Tax deductions once working.</strong> Claim up to 72% of exam fees as a tax deduction after employment begins.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="ch-h3">Geographic considerations</h3>
      <p class="ch-body">Where you choose to work in Australia significantly impacts your career trajectory, visa speed and quality of life.</p>

      <div class="ch-compare2">
        <div class="ch-compare2-col">
          <div class="ch-compare2-label">Major Cities — Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane</div>
          <p><strong>Pros.</strong> Advanced facilities, specialist training, cultural diversity.</p>
          <p><strong>Cons.</strong> Higher competition, expensive living. Rent: $600 – $800 per week.</p>
          <p><strong>Best for.</strong> Subspecialty training and urban lifestyle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ch-compare2-col">
          <div class="ch-compare2-label">Regional Centres — Geelong, Newcastle, Townsville</div>
          <p><strong>Pros.</strong> Higher IMG acceptance, faster visa sponsorship, 15% salary bonus.</p>
          <p><strong>Cons.</strong> Limited specialist services, smaller social networks.</p>
          <p><strong>Best for.</strong> General practice, faster PR pathway, family lifestyle.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

